{"word":"H6279 - עָתַר - ʻâthar - aw-thar' - Intreat","slug":"H6279","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">עָתַר</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>ʻâthar"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>aw-thar'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Intreat"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05E2;&#x05EA;&#x05E8; - &#x201B;a&#x0302;thar</b> - <i>aw-thar'</i><p/>A primitive root (rather denominative from <a href=\"#/H6281\">H6281</a>); to burn <i>incense</i> in worship, that is, <i>intercede</i> (reciprocally <i>listen</i> to prayer): - intreat, (make) pray (-er)."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H6282\">H6282</a>"}]}